<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920109-0142</DOCNO><DOCID>920109-0142.</DOCID><HL>   Gantos Inc. Sales Increase</HL><DATE>01/09/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GTOS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)SPECIALTY APPAREL RETAILERS (SAP)</IN><RE>MICHIGAN (MI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. -- Gantos Inc. said it had sales of$40.1 million for the five-week period ended Saturday, up 17%from sales of $34.2 million a year earlier. Same-store salesincreased 19%.   Sales for the 48 weeks ended Saturday rose 4% to $243.1million from $234.1 million a year earlier. Same-store saleswere unchanged.</LP><TEXT>   Gantos, a women's apparel retailer, adjusted its salesfigures to exclude net sales from catalog operations, whichwere discontinued during the first quarter of 1991.</TEXT></DOC>